Phrase: Versailles joined us, and the unit responsible for entering Hinayashiki to rescue Miyako was reorganised. We had another strategy meeting and decided to plan how we would breaktrough Hinayashiki.
The key to this strategy is, of course, Yuuzen.

If Yuuzen is unable to open the Gate leading to Hinayashiki, the operation to rescue Miyako will have to be immediately cancelled. The information that the Phantom Mist is expanding at the target location cannot be overlooked. Using the Gate to teleport directly into the mansion is an absolute prerequisite for this operation.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I understand the story. If Miss Yuuzen has the power, she can open the Gate again at the top of Senbon Torii.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: There is no guarantee that it will work. However, it should be possible to successfully disarm and re-utilize a barrier enchantment of that magnitude. At the very least, it should be possible to avoid being caught in a trap ourselves.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I'm thinking it's possible for everyone to jump in if we can manage the traps and sorceries set up at the Gate. However, did Miyako say to 'don't ever come'?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: No, I don't remember her saying it that way. She just said it would be difficult for anyone other than herself to go to Hinayashiki.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Miyako was aware of the trap at the gate. She knew that if we chased after her, we would all be torn apart.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miyako doesn't mince her words or say random things. I know she sounds a bit harsh when you're not used to listen to her. But Miyako's words are more trustworthy than anything else because she only tells the truth and what she really feels.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: If she said, 'Don't come to Hinayashiki', she would have said so. From the way Miyako said it, the problem isn't going to Hinayashiki, but going inside the Gate.

Name: Putra
Phrase: You said she was not good at speaking, but the result she conveyed is easy to understand.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's good that it's easy to understand. I trust that type of person more than those who blur the truth with a lot of unnecessary jargon.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: All that's left is to make a decision. It's almost possible to break the trap set by the enemy. I'm even a little doubtful that we can open the Gate without repercussions.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's even possible that we will be sent somewhere else other than Hinayashiki. Ya know what that means, don't cha?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: We'll be thrown out into the middle of the Mist.

Name: Putra
Phrase: And we won't even know where we are.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: I can't be responsible for that. If I am no longer of any use to ya, ya'll have no way of getting back to where ya were.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: If ya want to go, go now. I want Yoshino's assistance if possible. I think I can manage a little with my sorcery, but I can't wait for her to recover to full strength.

So we can only ask Yuuzen for a one-way ticket. Depending on the situation, there will also be situations where we will have to protect Yoshino. There is no guarantee that everyone will return safely.
The question is whether we are prepared to take on the challenge with that kind of intention. That is, to do it or not to do it. I have to make that decision here and now.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Mah, that's what I mean. If we take our time, we might end up doing more work than we need to.
I want to say this from my own mouth. I want you all to listen very carefully.
Going from the Gate at the top of the mountain to Hinayashiki does not only mean relying on Yuuzen's power.
...First and foremost, It means putting Yuuzen's life in danger.

Yuuzen is not a member of the Special Steel Squad, nor is she affiliated with the Allied Forces. She is an individual travelling the world to fulfil her own ends. The fact that she was a member of the Resistance does not disappear either. As such, she is not someone who we can be assured that she is completely trustworthy.
Nevertheless, Yuuzen says she will do it.
Whether she succeeds or fails, the risk is highest for Yuuzen, the sorceress. Yuuzen has told us not to complain if we die, but remember that it is Yuuzen who risks her life more than anyone else.
With what I've said so far, I would like everyone to vote for themselves - Do you want to go to Hinayashiki with Yuuzen?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino will go.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Yoshino, are you feeling better already?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: To be honest. A bit sick.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: But Yoshino's fine. Can do what's had always been done.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: If we were to leave, it would be immediately after this. Can you still say ya can go?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, Yoshino can. Been sleeping with that plan in mind.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino heard what Shashou said. He's right, everyone. What Yuuzen is trying to do is very, very dangerous.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Probably, it's even more dangerous than Shashou thinks. Yuuzen's life is more at risk than Yoshino and friends".

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's certainly dangerous, but it's not something to worry about. If ya're travelling alone, ya're bound to run into this kind of danger every now and then.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino's not that worried about it, Yuuzen. Yoshino is a sorceress. Can at least understand that you're risking your life to dispel the trap.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: That's only if I'm the one to do it, alright? I don't make the same mistake as a novice sorcerer like ya. The difference between my experience and yours is too great. Up to ya to believe me or not.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino believes in you.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Then you should try it the way I think it should be done. This is the only way to rescue Miyako. Unless ya're waiting for Miyako to come back.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Once the Nacht is over, we won't get another chance until the next Nacht. We don't have time to dawdle here.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Yuuzen, is it true that you can do something about Miss Yoshino's illness with your sorcery?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Yes, it's true. There will be recoil when the effect wears off, but if ya're still willing to continue, I can manage.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Wait a minute. What do you mean by 'recoil'? Will Yoshino's body be affected in any way?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: I can't say what exactly will happen, but there is no doubt that it will have a negative effect. After we finish this job, she won't be able to move for a while.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Well, it's not life-threatening. I promise ya that. It'll probably just give your body a bit of a workout.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: It's too dangerous. I wouldn't take her on an operation like this, let alone a regular mission.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Tell me, what is a regular mission?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Don't be so lenient with those who carry the lives of others on their shoulders. Ya SSS put your lives on the line every day, don't cha? Is the train Ricardo built simply a 'vehicle of convenience'?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: I know that. I know that much. But I'm sure the conditions vary from mission to mission.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yakky-tan, Yoshino is fine.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yoshino...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: If Yoshino doesn't have to go, then will not go. But this time, Yoshino has to be there for this sakusen. Yuuzen knows that too, so she wants to take Yoshino with her.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yuuzen. Can you cast that charm so that Yoshino can move a bit more? After saving Miyako, will rest for a while.'

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Understood. Then come over here.

Having conditionally removed Yoshino's ailment, Yuuzen immediately touched Yoshino's body and began chanting some kind of mysterious incantation. Something invisible entered Yoshino's body through Yuuzen's palm.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Child who does not know day should play at night. Swim across the river before you are caught.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Child that does not know night should play in the day. If you get caught, call someone from the bridge.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: If you follow, you will never know tiredness. If you follow the defilement, you will not know the moonlit night...
What is going on? Even if I understand what Yoshino meant by the word "charm", the rituals performed by Nishikese sorceresses are too foreign for me to understand.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Yoshino, did Miyako told ya anything about water? I think she probably told ya not to 'drink the water'.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: She told me. But Yoshino went crazy and wanted to drink water, so Yoshino jumped into a puddle with nagashi-bina floating in it.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Ya've been put under a very strong curse. But don't worry. Ya can drink this water.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Understand. If Yuuzen says so, will drink it.

Yuuzen took a bamboo tube out from her luggage and slowly poured its contents into a teacup. She circled the cup of water around Yoshino's head a couple of times, and took a sip before handing it back to Yoshino.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Did ya drink all of it?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yes, certainly. Obviously it was dubious water, but it's drunk.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Yoshino, what do you think? Did you notice any changes?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Did it taste good? Did you feel a hundred times better?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: To put it another way, what Yoshino drank was definitely not water. It was so bad that it can be said as that.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Hey, Yuuzen! What did you make Yoshino drink?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: It's special water with a strong curse on it. If ya're not a person of Nishiki, ya'll faint after just one sip.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Ugh, it's so disgusting. Yoshino feels like all my internal organs are going to come out through the earholes.

Name: Putra
Phrase: That's not good. It's true that Yoshino's ears are big, but I don't want that to happen.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Do ya feel a cracking pain in yer head or a dizzying sensation?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino gets them a lot. It's like falling down a flight of stairs after drinking a lot of alcohol.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Good. Then it worked.

Name: Putra
Phrase: It's a success!?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: That's the way it is. Ya'll feel better soon and will be able to use yer magic as usual.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Oh, now that you mention it, Yoshino has a feeling that's the case.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Really...?

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: As I said before, after the effect of the charm wears off, there will be serious recoil. Of course, the longer ya stay in Hinayashiki, the worse it will be.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: So we'll go quickly, kidnap Miyako and return. It's not a good pattern to both look for the owner of the mansion and getting locked inside. Don't forget that ya have a time limit.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino understands. Will find Miyako and rescue her as soon as possible.

Yoshino was brought back into the line of fire thanks to Yuuzen's sorcery. However, there seems to be a time limit on the effects of the charm, and if we don't get this done quickly, Yoshino may be stuck in Hinayashiki.

Name: Yuuzen
Phrase: Yeah, I'd like us to go without stopping if possible...
